org.chronos.chronodb.api.dump

Class ChronoDBDumpFormat

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.chronos.chronodb.api.dump.ChronoDBDumpFormat

  • public class ChronoDBDumpFormat
extends java.lang.Object
    This class describes the file format for DB dumps.

    This class serves two major purposes:

    • Offering constants and a default configuration for the file format
    • Creating input and output streams

      • createOutput

        public static ObjectOutput createOutput(java.io.File outputFile,
                                        DumpOptions options)
        Creates a default ObjectOutput for DB dumping .

        It is strongly recommended (and in some cases required) to use the same options for writing and reading a dump file!

        Parameters:
        outputFile - The file to store the dump data. Must not be null, must refer to a file. Will be created if it does not exist. Will be overwritten without further notice.
        options - The options to use when writing the dump. Must not be null, may be empty.
        Returns:
        The object output. Must be closed explicitly by the caller. Never null.
        Throws:
        ChronoDBStorageBackendException - When an I/O related error occurs.

      • createInput

        public static ObjectInput createInput(java.io.File inputFile,
                                      DumpOptions options)
        Creates a default ObjectInput for reading DB dump files.

        It is strongly recommended (and in some cases required) to use the same options for writing and reading a dump file!

        Parameters:
        inputFile - The dump file to read. Must not be null. Must point to a file (not a directory). Must point to an existing file.
        options - The options to use when reading the dump data. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        The object input. Must be closed explicitly by the caller. Never null.
        Throws:
        ChronoDBStorageBackendException - When an I/O related error occurs.
